{"type":"message","id":"db34c2cc","parentId":"39162940","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:45:45.414Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g4pvnspj8pdn_6","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { Joi } from 'express-validation';\n\nconst isString = Joi.string().optional().allow('', null);\n\nconst objectIdPattern = /^[0-9a-fA-F]{24}$/;\nconst isObjectID = Joi.string().pattern(objectIdPattern).required();\n\n//\n// Body schemas\n//\nconst createInternalCostBody = Joi.object({\n    cost: Joi.number().default(0),\n    type_id: isString,\n    payment_date: Joi.date().default(() => new Date()),\n    confirmed_id: isString,\n    is_paid: Joi.boolean(),\n    note: isString,\n    resource_id: isString.default(null),\n});\n\nconst updateInternalCostBody = Joi.object({\n    cost: Joi.number(),\n    type_id: isString,\n    payment_date: Joi.date(),\n    confirmed_id: isString,\n    is_paid: Joi.boolean(),\n    note: isString,\n    resource_id: isString,\n});\n\n//\n// express-validation schemas\n//\nexport const getById = {\n    params: Joi.object({\n        id: isObjectID,\n    }),\n};\n\nexport const deleteInternalCost = {\n    params: Joi.object({\n        id: isObjectID,\n    }),\n};\n\nexport const createInternalCost = {\n    body: createInternalCostBody,\n};\n\nexport const updateInternalCost = {\n    params: Joi.object({\n        id: isObjectID,\n    }),\n    body: updateInternalCostBody,\n};"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3994,"aggregated":"import { Joi } from 'express-validation';\n\nconst isString = Joi.string().optional().allow('', null);\n\nconst objectIdPattern = /^[0-9a-fA-F]{24}$/;\nconst isObjectID = Joi.string().pattern(objectIdPattern).required();\n\n//\n// Body schemas\n//\nconst createInternalCostBody = Joi.object({\n    cost: Joi.number().default(0),\n    type_id: isString,\n    payment_date: Joi.date().default(() => new Date()),\n    confirmed_id: isString,\n    is_paid: Joi.boolean(),\n    note: isString,\n    resource_id: isString.default(null),\n});\n\nconst updateInternalCostBody = Joi.object({\n    cost: Joi.number(),\n    type_id: isString,\n    payment_date: Joi.date(),\n    confirmed_id: isString,\n    is_paid: Joi.boolean(),\n    note: isString,\n    resource_id: isString,\n});\n\n//\n// express-validation schemas\n//\nexport const getById = {\n    params: Joi.object({\n        id: isObjectID,\n    }),\n};\n\nexport const deleteInternalCost = {\n    params: Joi.object({\n        id: isObjectID,\n    }),\n};\n\nexport const createInternalCost = {\n    body: createInternalCostBody,\n};\n\nexport const updateInternalCost = {\n    params: Joi.object({\n        id: isObjectID,\n    }),\n    body: updateInternalCostBody,\n};","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776149145214}}
{"type":"message","id":"988eb792","parentId":"db34c2cc","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:46:11.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me start the API testing. I'll first login, then systematically test all endpoints.\n\nLet me organize the full endpoint list:\n\n**Auth (no auth required):**\n- POST /api/v1/auth/signin\n- PATCH /api/v1/auth/change-password\n- POST /api/v1/auth/refetch-token\n\n**Guests (no auth):**\n- POST /api/v1/guests\n- POST /api/v1/guests/leads\n- GET /api/v1/guests\n- GET /api/v1/guests/:id\n\n\n- PATCH /api/v1/guests/:id\n- DELETE /api/v1/guests/:id\n\n**Devices (no auth):**\n- POST /api/v1/devices\n- GET /api/v1/devices\n- GET /api/v1/devices/:id\n- PATCH /api/v1/devices/:id\n- DELETE /api/v1/devices/:id\n\n**Users (auth required):**\n- POST /api/v1/users\n- GET /api/v1/users/role\n- GET /api/v1/users/:id\n- PATCH /api/v1/users/:id\n- PATCH /api/v1/users/:id\n\n/role\n- PATCH /api/v1/users/:id/restore\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers\n- POST /api/v1/users/teachers\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id\n- PATCH /api/v1/users/teachers/:id\n- DELETE /api/v1/users/teachers/:id\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/students\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/lessons\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/lessons/detail\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/exams\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/exams/detail\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/payments\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/payments/total\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/work-time\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/internal-costs/vehicle\n- GET /api/v1/users/teachers/:id/internal-costs/vehicle/total\n\nNow looking at the student endpoints, which include listing students by filter, creating new ones, retrieving individual student records, and various lesson and exam details associated with each student. Continuing with the sales endpoints for retrieving sales data, payment information, and managing counter assignments, then moving into the leads management section with create, update, and delete operations.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the role-based access control endpoints for creating and managing user roles, including bulk operations for assigning or removing roles from users. Continuing through the course-related endpoints, including fetching courses by student or ID, updating and deleting courses, then moving into course-student assignments with filtering and label support. Finishing up the lesson routes and moving into lesson type endpoints, then continuing with the teacher license category assignments. Continuing through the exams endpoints, I'm mapping out the remaining routes for retrieving individual exams, updating them with notifications, and handling deletions. Moving into exam results now. Now I'm looking at the remaining exam schedules endpoints and moving into exam registrations, which handle student sign-ups for exams with create, update, and delete operations, plus dedicated routes for retrieving a student's own registrations. Now I'm looking at the remaining teacher comment endpoints for retrieving, updating, and deleting individual comments, then moving into the vehicles module which handles fleet management including vehicle listings and creation. Continuing through the payment endpoints and moving into stadium management routes, which handle basic CRUD operations for stadium locations. I'm continuing through the lead management endpoints, then moving into internal cost structure routes that handle both vehicle and office expense categories with their respective totals. Continuing through the notification configuration and content management endpoints, then moving into the notifies module which handles scheduled and mobile notification delivery. I'm continuing through the notification endpoints for user notifications and mobile pushes, then moving into convention-related routes. I notice the convention route is incomplete—it's just a POST endpoint that should probably have a base route defined. Let me start testing the API with authentication and work through the endpoints systematically.","thinkingSignature":"ae185d9d7d980c499d56c18c7a76f7c92388c008b4fd062a5f79c4c9e32262d0"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me start the systematic API testing. First, login:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zo8x8e6u8b5k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/signin \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Admin123!\"}'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":4443,"output":966,"cacheRead":15700,"cacheWrite":10859,"totalTokens":31968,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776149145414,"responseId":"062d159b4a5deb40384fe95d14bbdf5b"}}
